                    <p class='MsoNormal' style='margin-top:0in;margin-right:1.45pt;margin-bottom: 12.4pt;margin-left:.5pt'>Consumers have the option of signing the Charter of Aged Care Rights (the Charter). Consumers can receive care and services even if they choose not to sign.&nbsp;</p>
                    <p class='MsoNormal' style='margin-top:0in;margin-right:1.45pt;margin-bottom: 14.1pt;margin-left:.5pt'>If a consumer decides to sign the Charter, they are acknowledging that their provider has given them a copy of the Charter, and assisted them to understand:</p>
